 3. CODE DUPLICATION
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

[DUP-01] LM Studio URL parsing duplicated 4 times
  File: src/main/ipc/register-llm-handlers.js
    - buildLmstudioEndpoint()           lines 232-250
    - getLmstudioLoadedInstanceConfig() lines 271-297  (inline URL parsing)
    - buildLmstudioNativeModelsEndpoint() lines 299-312
    - enforceLmstudioLoadedConfig()     lines 314-391  (inline URL parsing)
  
  Each one does the same: parse base URL, replace localhost→127.0.0.1,
  strip trailing /v1, build endpoint path. Four copies means four places
  to fix if the URL format changes.
  
  Fix: Extract `buildLmstudioUrl(baseUrl, apiPath)` and reuse it.


[DUP-02] HeadlessIpcBridge duplicated between main.js and docker-entry.js (REVISED)
  Files: src/main/main.js:35-53, src/main/docker-entry.js:23-37
  Both define a class with `handle()` and `invoke()` that wraps a Map.
  REVISED ANALYSIS: The main.js version (IpcBridge) wraps the real ipcMain AND
  stores handlers for local invocation. The docker-entry.js version (HeadlessIpcBridge)
  is standalone with no ipcMain dependency. They have the same interface but different
  implementations — one delegates to Electron, the other is self-contained.
  Extracting a shared base class is still valid but lower priority since the
  implementations are small (15-20 lines each) and serve different entry points.
  Severity: LOW (minor duplication, not a bug)


[DUP-03] SubtaskRuntime has massive private/non-private code duplication
  File: src/main/subtask-runtime.js
  Every lifecycle method (createRun, completeRun, failRun, cancelRun,
  deliverToParent) has a `if (privateRun) { ...nearly identical code... }`
  branch that copies 80% of the non-private logic. That's ~400 lines
  of near-duplicate code across 5 methods.


[DUP-04] Minimax/invoke XML cleanup regex duplicated
  Both shared-utils.js:52-53 AND tool-chain-controller.js:108-110
  have the same two regexes:
    .replace(/<minimax:tool_call>[\s\S]*?<\/minimax:tool_call>/gi, '')
    .replace(/<invoke\s+name\s*=\s*["'][^"']+["'][^>]*>[\s\S]*?<\/invoke>/gi, '')


[DUP-05] markUserActive/markUserIdle pattern
  The send-message handler (register-chat-data-handlers.js:694-696, 779-781)
  and interpret-tool-result handler (lines 792-794) have the exact same
  activity tracking preamble:
    if (!isTestSession && !isPrivateSession) {
        markUserActive(activitySessionId);
    }
  And finally block. Extract into a wrapper.


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 4. TEST COVERAGE GAPS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Current state: 77 contract tests in tests/contracts/ + 24 tool tests in tools/.
The contract tests are well-structured but the coverage has gaps:

[TEST-01] No test for database.js CRUD correctness
  The database-runtime-contract.test.js is only 400 bytes — likely just checks
  the module loads. There are NO tests for:
    - getConversations (especially the limit bug — BUG-03)
    - addConversation with metadata serialization
    - updateCustomTool (the code/input_schema bug — BUG-07)
    - setAPIKey / getAPIKey encryption round-trip
    - enqueueMemoryJob deduplication logic
    - claimNextMemoryJob transaction correctness
    - failMemoryJob retry/max-attempts logic
    - getCurrentSession auto-creation fallback
    - deleteAllConversations cascade

[TEST-02] No test for the 3 stripToolPatterns implementations
  The tool-chain-controller-contract.test.js exists (8.8KB) but only tests
  the chaining logic. The 3 different strip implementations (BUG-01) are
  never compared against each other. Need:
    - Nested brace test: TOOL:run_command{"cmd":"echo {x}"}
    - Unicode content test
    - Malformed/unclosed JSON test
    - Minimax XML format test
    - Test that all 3 implementations give the same result

[TEST-03] No test for ConnectorRuntime
  No contract test exists for connector lifecycle (start, stop, worker
  message handling, RPC dispatch, startup timeout). This is code that
  spawns worker threads and has complex message passing.

[TEST-04] No test for BackgroundMemoryDaemon
  background-memory-daemon-*-contract tests exist (3 files) but they're
  small (1.1KB, 2.5KB, 1.6KB). The daemon has complex logic:
    - Escalating tick intervals
    - Resource gate checking
    - User activity deferral
    - Job queue draining
    - LLM-driven task selection
    - State persistence
  Most of this is untested.

[TEST-05] No test for BackendEventBus inference dispatch
  No test verifies that events with `needsInference: true` actually
  reach the LLM and that the silent/notify decision works.

[TEST-06] No test for InferenceDispatcher lane-based scheduling
  The inference-concurrency-contract.test.js (5.6KB) exists but the
  actual `_executeScheduled` queue chaining logic — which is the most
  critical concurrency primitive — needs edge case tests:
    - Two parallel calls to the same lane
    - Error in one queued call doesn't block the next
    - Lane cleanup when the last promise settles

[TEST-07] No integration test for send-message end-to-end
  The full send-message flow (IPC → history load → dispatch → chain
  controller → tool execution → persist response) is the core user
  feature but has no end-to-end test with a mocked LLM. The
  test-ipc-flow-mocked.js exists but is a tool/ script, not a
  proper test.

[TEST-08] No test for agent deletion cascade (BUG-02)
  No test verifies that deleting an agent cleans up:
    - Agent folder
    - Agent sessions
    - Subagent runs
    - Tool permission profile

[TEST-09] No test for PluginManager managed process lifecycle
  plugin-lifecycle-contract.test.js exists (7.3KB) but managed process
  registration, the SIGTERM→SIGKILL sequence, and the emergency hooks
  are not covered.

[TEST-10] Test runner is custom, not a standard framework
  File: tests/run-suite.js + tests/helpers/assert.js
  The project uses a hand-rolled test runner with a custom assert module.
  This means:
    - No parallel test execution
    - No test filtering/grep
    - No watch mode
    - No coverage reporting
    - No snapshot testing
    - No mocking utilities beyond manual stubs
  
  The 77 contract tests and 24 tool tests would benefit from migration
  to vitest or jest for better DX and CI integration.


